                                                                <customfield id="customfield_12310192" key="com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:textarea">
                        <customfieldname>Release Note</customfieldname>
                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>Previous to this fix Pig would not start any new MapReduce jobs once the Pig controlling process was killed, but it would not stop any currently running MapReduce jobs.  Now it will attempt to kill running MapReduce jobs also.  Note that under certain conditions this will still fail, such as when Pig is killed with a KILL signal and does not have a chance to call its shutdown hooks.</customfieldvalue>

